This paper deals with the training of convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of batch normalization is a technique for improving the training of neural networks, which falls under the category of optimization algorithms (cs.NE). The paper also discusses how the position of the batch normalization layer can affect the training of different networks, which is relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves experimentation and analysis of the results, which could be considered as a form of natural language processing (cs.CL).
